resourceAbstractObject.default: Data from the 'Animal communities observatory' (OCOA): Observation of animal communities (birds, reptiles, amphibians, coprophages, ...): standardized periodic surveys and georeferenced in Languedoc-Roussillon.. This observatory is part of the Montpellier Research Observatory of Environment (OSU OREME, oreme.org). It consists in different observing tasks: Beetles ; Bird communities ; Freshwater molluscs communities ; Reptiles and amphibians ; Temporary water points.
